      "part_type": "Hadith",
      "path": "/books/al-kafi:7:3:61:13",
      "relations": null,
      "text": [
        " قُلْتُ لِأَبِي عَبْدِ اللَّهِ ( عليه السلام ) إِنَّ بَزِيعاً يَزْعُمُ أَنَّهُ نَبِيٌّ فَقَالَ إِنْ سَمِعْتَهُ يَقُولُ ذَلِكَ فَاقْتُلْهُ قَالَ فَجَلَسْتُ لَهُ غَيْرَ مَرَّةٍ فَلَمْ يُمْكِنِّي ذَلِكَ ."
      ],
      "translations": {
        "en.hubeali": [
          "Muhammad Bin Yahya, from Ahmad Bin Muhammad, from Ibn Fazal, from Hammad Bin Usman, from Ibn Abu Yafour who said, ",
          "‘I said to Abu Abdullah<sup>asws</sup> that, Baziya alleges that he is a Prophet. So he<sup>asws</sup> said: ‘If you were to hear him saying that, you should kill him’. He said, ‘So I sat with (awaiting) for him many a time, but was not able over that’."
        ]
      }
    }
